Aedeagus (Fig. 6
A-D
) 5.4 mm long; median lobe stout, expanded ventrally in median part; apical branch short, obtuse and bisinuate at apex; subapical branch long, evenly curved apically; tegmen not movable, with short tegminal strut; endophallus consisting of bifid long right membranous lobe and left membranous lobe, with rather sclerotized spinous plate at base of left lobe.
